description: Ms. written in Paris for a personage named Philippus. In Latin; calendar and most rubrics in French. Five large miniatures have been attributed to the workshop or to a follower of the Boucicaut Master. Purchased from J.M. Winkler, Baltimore, 1922. Formerly purchased at Charleston, S.C., in 1807 by Robert Gilmor, Jr., of Baltimore. Imperfect: One or more leaves following the leaves numbered in modern pencil 51, 54, 58, 73, 118 and 212 wanting, with a loss of text and illustration. Library of Congress.  Medieval and Renaissance ms. bks., 56 Ricci, S. de.  Medieval and Renaissance mss., p. 235, no. 120 Ricci, S. de.  Medieval and Renaissance mss. (suppl.), p. 120, no. 92 Cataloged as a manuscript. vj46 10-02-91
